''angulókë'' is a [[Quenya]] noun meaning "dragon".<ref name=LR370/>

According to the Quenya style of ''[[The Lord of the Rings]]'', it would be written as ''anguló'''c'''ë''.<ref>[[Helge Fauskanger]], ''[http://folk.uib.no/hnohf/Quettaparma.pdf Quettaparma Quenyallo]'' (accessed 9 December 2010)</ref>

==Etymology==
It derives from the [[Elvish]] [[Sundocarme|roots]] [[ANGWA|ANGU]] and [[LOK]].<ref name=LR370>{{LR|Etymologies}}, entry "[[LOK]]"</ref>
